Users Manager
Tech Stack

    Node.js
    Express.js
    MongoDB
    Mongoose
    nodemon
    React

    Documentation can be found in docs folder.

Prepare The Environment

    Create a new MongoDB database with a cards collection.
    Clone project in vscode: https://github.com/levworkshop/users.git

Project Installation

    Install nodemon globally: npm i -g nodemon and update package.json accordingly.
    Server:
        Add configuration file: config/dev.js containing the database connection details.
        Install dependencies for the Server:
        cd server
        npm install
    Install dependencies for React client:
    cd client
    npm install

Run The App

    Make sure mongo server is running.

    Run the server - cd server, then:
        Windows: SET DEBUG=users:* & npm start
        MacOS/Linux: DEBUG=users:* npm start
    Run the client:
    cd client
    npm start
